main event: On March 6, 1963, an object was observed in Duluth, Minnesota, which exploded and disappeared after being seen at a high elevation.
interesting points: The observed object was similar to a large flare, and appeared to explode and break up,Duration of the observation was about 1 minute and 30 seconds, The object was first seen at 60 degrees elevation and 270 degrees azimuth, The object emitted a bright white color that turned red, Witnesses described the object as being the same size as an aircraft at the horizon, The site was a location of multiple reported sightings of unexplained phenomena.
sighted object: one exploding object resembling a flare
witness description: Unknown, but multiple people observed the incident
